<subSubSection id="C34E6527FF6B2EAC64AFFB7BD685CEC8" pageId="135" pageNumber="136" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8BEB36ACFF6B2EAC64AFFB7BD685CEC8" blockId="135.[151,1437,966,1279]" pageId="135" pageNumber="136">
<emphasis id="B920EABEFF6B2EAC64AFFB7BD37BCEEC" bold="true" box="[199,308,1218,1243]" pageId="135" pageNumber="136">Remarks</emphasis>
. The most similar species are 
<taxonomicName id="4C544D2FFF6B2EAC66EDFB7BD127CEEC" baseAuthorityName="Sars" baseAuthorityYear="1870" box="[645,872,1218,1243]" class="Malacostraca" family="Lampropidae" genus="Platysympus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cumacea" pageId="135" pageNumber="136" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="typicus">
<emphasis id="B920EABEFF6B2EAC66EDFB7BD127CEEC" box="[645,872,1218,1243]" italics="true" pageId="135" pageNumber="136">Platysympus typicus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C544D2FFF6B2EAC67F6FB7DD672CEEC" authorityName="Hansen" authorityYear="1920" box="[926,1085,1220,1243]" class="Malacostraca" family="Lampropidae" genus="Platysympus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cumacea" pageId="135" pageNumber="136" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tricarinatus">
<emphasis id="B920EABEFF6B2EAC67F6FB7DD672CEEC" box="[926,1085,1220,1243]" italics="true" pageId="135" pageNumber="136">P. tricarinatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, which can be differented from 
<taxonomicName id="4C544D2FFF6B2EAC64FFFB5ED350CEC8" authorityName="Day" authorityYear="1978" box="[151,287,1254,1279]" class="Malacostraca" family="Lampropidae" genus="Platysympus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cumacea" pageId="135" pageNumber="136" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="depressus">
<emphasis id="B920EABEFF6B2EAC64FFFB5ED350CEC8" box="[151,287,1254,1279]" italics="true" pageId="135" pageNumber="136">P. depressus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the presence of a mid–dorsal ridge. In 
<taxonomicName id="4C544D2FFF6B2EAC6690FB5ED1CECEC8" authorityName="Day" authorityYear="1978" box="[760,897,1254,1279]" class="Malacostraca" family="Lampropidae" genus="Platysympus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cumacea" pageId="135" pageNumber="136" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="depressus">
<emphasis id="B920EABEFF6B2EAC6690FB5ED1CECEC8" box="[760,897,1254,1279]" italics="true" pageId="135" pageNumber="136">P. depressus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
there is no mid–dorsal ridge.
</paragraph>
